benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/phase - Retrieve phase for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid Request: Happy path with subscriptionId + requestedDate returns 200 and application/json Phase object (TC01).
Query Parameters: Broad combinations tested — missing, invalid formats, and unsupported extras (TC02–TC08, TC14).
Empty/Not Found: Non-existent subscription, out-of-range date, and empty DB return 404 variants (TC05, TC08, TC12).
Error Handling: Invalid parameter formats return 400; dependency failure returns 503; injection attempts are rejected without leaking internals (TC06, TC07, TC10, TC11).
Edge/Boundary: Phase change boundary date behavior verified (TC15).
Performance/Concurrency: Large dataset performance and concurrent requests tested (TC13, TC16).
Produces/Content-Type: application/json verified on success path (TC01).
Pagination: Not applicable to this single-resource endpoint.
gaps: Caching Behavior: No checks for ETag/Last-Modified/Cache-Control or conditional GET (If-None-Match) and 304 handling.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No scenarios validating 429 responses and Retry-After headers under burst traffic.
Response Schema Validation: "Valid Phase object" is not concretely validated against #/definitions/Phase (fields, types, nullability); error payload schema not asserted.
Content Negotiation and Headers: No tests for Accept variations (e.g., text/plain -> 406 or documented behavior) and consistent Content-Type on error responses.
Ambiguity in TC02: Expected outcome when only subscriptionId is provided is not deterministic ("200 or default phase"); needs a clear, asserted contract.
Parameter Edge Cases: Missing coverage for empty-string values, leading/trailing whitespace, UUID case sensitivity, and tricky dates (e.g., 2021-02-29, timezone offsets when only a date is allowed).
Consistency of headers: Content-Type and charset are only asserted in TC01; other success and error paths don’t verify headers.
recommendations: Add caching tests: verify Cache-Control and ETag on 200; re-issue request with If-None-Match to expect 304 or confirm documented behavior if caching is disabled.
Add rate limiting tests: fire a burst of requests to trigger or confirm absence of 429; if present, assert Retry-After and rate-limit headers.
Strengthen schema assertions: validate the Phase JSON matches #/definitions/Phase (required fields, types, enums); validate a standard Error schema for 4xx/5xx.
Clarify and codify behavior for omitted parameters (esp. only subscriptionId). Update TC02 to assert a single expected status and payload per API contract.
Add content negotiation scenarios: request with Accept: application/json (200) and with unsupported Accept (expect 406 or documented fallback).
Add parameter robustness tests: empty string and whitespace values, uppercase/lowercase UUIDs, invalid calendar dates (e.g., 2021-02-29), and timezone-suffixed inputs rejected when format is date.
Verify headers on all paths: assert Content-Type on success and error responses; optionally assert no sensitive details in error messages.
